{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/init(_:isOn:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/init(_:tableName:bundle:isOn:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:)"],"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/body"],"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/View-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Switch item is a UI element that allows to toggle between two states, typically “On” and “Off”, and used to enable or disable features, options or settings.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Switch Item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"content":[{"text":"Layouts","type":"heading","anchor":"Layouts","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inverse"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": like the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" layout but with a trailing switch indicator and a leading optional decorative icon","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Indicator states","type":"heading","anchor":"Indicator-states","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The switch indicator has two available states set as a boolean property that determines whether the toggle is on or off."}]},{"text":"Particular cases","type":"heading","anchor":"Particular-cases","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem"},{"type":"text","text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isError"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem"},{"type":"text","text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as disabled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The switch can be also outlined in some cases."}]},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Voice Over","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and optional texts and a custom switch trait."}]},{"text":"Forbidden by design","type":"heading","anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"text":"Code samples","type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected state","    @Published var isOn: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSSwitchItem(LocalizedStringKey(\"notifications_setting\"), bundle: Bundle.module, isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, and a description text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A leading switch with an additional label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A trailing switch with a label, an additional label, a description text and an icon.","    \/\/ The inverse layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   description: \"The Beatles\",","                   isReversed: true,","                   icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ A trailing switch with a label, a description text, an icon, a divider and is about an error.","    \/\/ The inverse layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   description: \"Put your hand in mine\",","                   icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"),","                   isReversed: true,","                   isError: true,","                   hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   isError: true,","                   errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                   hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\", isOn: $isOn)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related switch as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $isOn, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, flipLeadingIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"text":"Design documentation","type":"heading","anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-switch"}]},{"text":"Themes rendering","type":"heading","anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2},{"text":"Orange","type":"heading","anchor":"Orange","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_Orange"}]},{"text":"Orange Compact","type":"heading","anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_OrangeCompact"}]},{"text":"Sosh","type":"heading","anchor":"Sosh","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_Sosh"}]},{"text":"Wireframe","type":"heading","anchor":"Wireframe","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_Wireframe"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Version","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.5.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Since","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.14.0","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsswitchitem"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"platforms":[{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"15.0"},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"13.0"},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"16.0"},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0"},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"11.0"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents14OUDSSwitchItemV","title":"OUDSSwitchItem","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure"},"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSSwitchItem":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSSwitchItem"}],"title":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Switch item is a UI element that allows to toggle between two states, typically “On” and “Off”, and used to enable or disable features, options or settings.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Switch Item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsswitchitem","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"key